{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 887930, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "afflok", "body": "Vindicator Maraad is the Draenei in the BC cinematic and appears to be wearing Paladin T4 armor ([url=http://www.wowhead.com/?itemsets&filter=cl=2;ta=12]Justicar[/url]), a two-handed mace ([url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=28800]Hammer of the Naaru[/url]), and some other Karazhan gear.  Here is an [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?compare=29071:29072:29074:29075:29073:28800:28512:28733:28569;32648;29375]item comparison[/url] with all the gear he's wearing.  Click on the drop-down menu on the item group's control bar and hit View in 3D on Male Draenei if you don't believe me.  \n\nNotes on item selection: \n[small]1. FEET: The boots that best fit the color scheme of the Justicar gear don't have the symbol which can be seen on Maraad's boots.  There is another pair of boots which does have the symbol, and actually follows a closer color scheme to Maraad's (which has the same model as Justicar, but not exactly the same colors), so I can't decide which looks better in trying to recreate Maraad.  You can easily trade one pair of boots for the other in my item comparison by simply dragging and dropping - then view in 3D again to see the difference.  \n2. HEAD: Maraad is not shown to be wearing the headpiece, but I included one because it's part of the set.  What appears on his forehead instead is the visual effect of the Draenei Racial called [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=28880#.]Gift of the Naaru[/url].  Drag the headpiece out of the set if you don't like it in your model viewer.\n3. BACK: There is a cloak that looks good with the set (included in my linked comparison), but Maraad isn't wearing any cloak.[/small]", "date": "2009-11-11T00:37:21-06:00", "rating": 33, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Maraad is not wearing standard Justicar shoulders. You'll notice the detail at the top of the Justicar shoulders that makes it look sorta like multiple plates is not on Maraad's. The glowing purple crystal on each shoulder is replaced with a line of glowing runes, and the the color scheme of the entire set is completely different (silver detail instead of gold). Nice try though.", "creationdate": "2011-12-23T06:04:39-06:00", "id": 500515, "rating": -2, "commentid": 887930, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Morrivar", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Great work, thank-you for this!", "creationdate": "2013-03-30T07:01:19-05:00", "id": 646854, "rating": 0, "commentid": 887930, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Fishbubbles", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Maraad *is* wearing a cloak in the BC cinematic \u2014 you can see it from about 1:19-1:21 here (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B8XtohlqEeM), but I'd be hard pressed to find something similar in game?", "creationdate": "2015-11-13T23:13:28-06:00", "id": 910900, "rating": 0, "commentid": 887930, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "BGilkison", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-03-01T22:20:15-06:00", 2, "afflok"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 1007415, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "FarseerLolotea", "body": "[quote]The one from the BC movie is Farseer Nobundo, before he became a Broken Draenei.[/quote]You mean in the cinematic?  I haven't seen [i]anything[/i] to support that claim.  \n\nAnd based on skin tone, facial features, etc., the vindicator from the cinematic [i]looks[/i] like Maraad.  (Aside from the beard, but that's a detail that would be easy enough to change.)  \n\nOf course, male draenei in promo art [i]do[/i] tend to end up fitting a specific pattern (medium blue, dark hair, four tendrils).  But if you take a look at the [i]Unbroken[/i] image, Nobundo had a differently shaped crest back when he still had one.", "date": "2010-03-28T20:10:58-05:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-03-28T20:15:03-05:00", 2, "FarseerLolotea"]}
